    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potato[es] </strong>(skins on) into fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peanut-satay-meat-free-hot-dog-ft-paprika-lime-sweet-potato-fries/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the fries are cooking, add your <strong>meat-free hot dog sausage[s]</strong> to one side of a separate baking tray (use<strong> tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!)</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 17-18 min or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 trays!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peanut-satay-meat-free-hot-dog-ft-paprika-lime-sweet-potato-fries/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, zest your<strong> lime</strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter)</p><p>Roll the <strong>zested lime[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut into 2 wedges per person</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks (save some leaves for garnish!)</p><p>Roughly chop your <strong>roasted peanuts</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peanut-satay-meat-free-hot-dog-ft-paprika-lime-sweet-potato-fries/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>peanut butter </strong>and <strong>soy sauce </strong>in a small bowl with your <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli relish</strong>, <strong>half </strong>of the <strong>chopped peanuts</strong> and the juice of <strong>half</strong> the <strong>lime wedges </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) \u2013 this is your <strong>satay sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peanut-satay-meat-free-hot-dog-ft-paprika-lime-sweet-potato-fries/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>mooli slaw mix</strong> and the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>to a large bowl with the juice of the <strong>remaining lime wedge[s]</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and set aside \u2013 this is your <strong>lime-pickled mooli slaw</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peanut-satay-meat-free-hot-dog-ft-paprika-lime-sweet-potato-fries/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut a slit into the top of your<strong> hot dog bun[s]</strong></p><p>Remove the sausage tray[s] from the oven and add the <strong>cut</strong> <strong>hot dog bun[s]</strong> to the other side of the tray[s], then return the tray[s] to the oven for 2-3 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peanut-satay-meat-free-hot-dog-ft-paprika-lime-sweet-potato-fries/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>ground paprika </strong>and the <strong>lime zest</strong> to a large bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Once the fries are golden and crisp add them to the bowl and give everything a good mix up \u2013 these are your<strong> paprika lime fries</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peanut-satay-meat-free-hot-dog-ft-paprika-lime-sweet-potato-fries/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Fill the <strong>warmed hot dog bun </strong>with a <strong>meat-free</strong> <strong>hot dog sausage</strong>, then top with some <strong>satay sauce</strong>, <strong>remaining chopped peanuts</strong>, <strong>reserved</strong> <strong>coriander leaves </strong>and some of the <strong>lime-pickled mooli slaw </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>meat-free peanut satay hot dog</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>paprika lime fries</strong>, the <strong>remaining lime-pickled mooli slaw</strong> and any <strong>remaining satay sauce </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
